Police are investigating the status of a gun recovered from acting head of Parking Service Management at City Hall Fredrick Ndunyu.Ndunyu was arrested on Wednesday afternoon and locked up at the Central police station for what was initially reported as being in possession of an unlicensed firearm.However, an officer from the station said Ndunyu was released on a police bond and did not record any statement.It's not clear why Ndunyu did not record a statement, but the officer, who requested anonymity, said the matter is being handled by the Central police DCIO."We are currently waiting for a report from the chief licensing officer on the authenticity of the weapon," the officer said.Ndunyu did not answer calls or respond to our text messages.